# .hypatia-ignore — repo-scoped exemptions for the estate governance
# bundle's anti-pattern scanner. Format (per the bundle's `is_exempt`
# function): each non-comment line is `${rule}:${path}` matched as a
# fixed-string whole-line equality (`grep -qxF`).
#
# Comment lines (`#`) and blank lines are tolerated because they never
# match the `rule:path` shape under -xF.
#
# ─── Coq-generated Makefiles (formal/) ─────────────────────────────
#
# The Coq formalisation under `formal/` is built with `coq_makefile`,
# the canonical Coq build-system generator (ships with the Coq
# distribution). It emits these three files unconditionally:
#
#   - formal/Makefile.coq       (main build rules, 32K, regenerated)
#   - formal/Makefile.coq.conf  (dependency tracking, regenerated)
#   - formal/Makefile.conf      (project config bridge)
#
# They are NOT hand-authored Makefiles. They are Coq's published
# convention for compiling .v files; replacing them with
# Mustfile/justfile would require porting the entire Coq build
# pipeline — out of scope and not actually wanted (Coq users expect
# `make -f Makefile.coq` to work).
#
# Exemption is path-based rather than inline-pragma because the files
# are regenerated by `coq_makefile` on every project structure change,
# and any inline pragma would be silently dropped on the next regen.
cicd_rules/banned_language_file:formal/Makefile.coq
cicd_rules/banned_language_file:formal/Makefile.coq.conf
cicd_rules/banned_language_file:formal/Makefile.conf

